The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Top partnerships
                                                   Top partnerships
                      
	Mahela Jayawardene (240) and Thilan Samaraweera (231) set a fourth-wicket Test record stand of 437 runs. Sri Lanka now hold the world record for the second, third, and fourth wickets in Test cricket. The following is the list of Lankan records:         
	2nd  S. Jayasuriya amp; R. Mahanama 576 (SL) vs Ind, Colombo, 1997-98         
	3rd  K. Sangakkara amp; M. Jayawardene 624 (SL) vs SA, Colombo, 2006         
	4th  M. Jayawardene amp; T. Samaraweera 437 (SL) vs Pak, Karachi, 2008-09         
	 There have been 15 instances in Test cricket where two batsmen have scored a double hundred in a single innings. On four occasions Sri Lankan batsmen have achieved this feat.           COMPILED BY MOHANDAS MENON                                                                                                                   
